      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 16:48:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI think the patch would be cleaner if you added __inode_sub_bytes() and __inode_get_bytes() helpers that assumed i_lock is already held, and had inode_sub_bytes() and inode_get_bytes() call those helpers, as well as the two places in the patch where these functions are open coded.\n\nOnce we get a final working version of this patch, I'll see if Jan Kara (quota msintainer) would be willing to include this into the upstream kernel.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
